ate">April 5, 2020</span><span itemprop="dateModified" content="2020-04-05T17:30:07.000Z"/></div><div class="article-tags-wrapper"><ul><li><a href="/news" class="article-tag" data-analytics="Content Tags News">News</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="news-body"><div class="hero-image"><div class="image-wrapper" style="padding-bottom: calc(1080/1920 * 100%)"><img class="image-fade-in"alt=""src="https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fapi.thedrive.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-05-at-11.27.22-AM.jpg%3Fquality%3D85?w=1440&amp;auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=8482c6e2333860c84dd7c80ea5101b16"srcset="https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fapi.thedrive.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-05-at-11.27.22-AM.jpg%3Fquality%3D85?w=1440&amp;auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=8482c6e2333860c84dd7c80ea5101b16 1x,https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fapi.thedrive.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-05-at-11.27.22-AM.jpg%3Fquality%3D85?w=1920&amp;auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=5bac0733b62729f77044db44fe16d7b3 1.5x"onload="this.style.opacity=1"/><figcaption class="full-bleed-image-credit">Mecum</figcaption></div></div><div class="article-social"><div class="article-social-container"><span class="article-social__share">SHARE</span><ul class="article-social__items"><li class="article-social__item"><a class="icon icon-twitter"data-social="twitter"href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fnews%2F32897%2Ftheres-no-limo-more-extreme-than-this-1m-learjet-turned-party-rig%3Fxid%3Dtwittershare"target="_blank"rel="nofollow"title="Share on Twitter"aria-label="Share on Twitter"data-analytics="Article Share Twitter"></a></li><li class="article-social__item"><a class="icon icon-facebook"data-social="facebook"href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fnews%2F32897%2Ftheres-no-limo-more-extreme-than-this-1m-learjet-turned-party-rig%3Fxid%3Dfbshare"target="_blank"rel="nofollow"title="Share on Facebook"aria-label="Share on Facebook"data-analytics="Article Share Facebook"></a></li><li class="article-social__item"><a class="icon icon-pinterest"data-social="pinterest"data-pin-do="buttonPin"data-pin-custom="true"href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fnews%2F32897%2Ftheres-no-limo-more-extreme-than-this-1m-learjet-turned-party-rig%3Fxid%3Dpinterestshare"target="_blank"rel="nofollow"title="Share on Pinterest"aria-label="Share on Pinterest"data-analytics="Article Share Pintrest"></a></li><li class="article-social__item"><a class="icon icon-email"href="mailto:?subject=Theres%20No%20Limo%20More%20Extreme%20Than%20This%20%241M%20Learjet-Turned-Party%20Rig&amp;body=https://www.thedrive.com/news/32897/theres-no-limo-more-extreme-than-this-1m-learjet-turned-party-rig?xid=emailshare"target="_blank"rel="nofollow"title="Share via Email"aria-label="Share via Email"data-analytics="Article Share Mail"></a></li></ul></div></div><div class="has-ad-column"><div class="ad-column"><div class="ad" data-ad-type="colAd"></div></div><div class="articleFragment paragraph"><p>The world is full of unlikely limo conversions. How about <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/26297/someone-turned-a-porsche-930-convertible-into-a-limo-and-now-theyre-selling-it" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">a long-wheelbase Porsche 930</a>, or <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/30386/turn-every-night-into-prom-night-with-this-chevy-impala-ss-limousine-for-just-5000" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">a Chevy Impala SS with a minibar inside</a>? Would a <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/31094/for-sale-restored-1988-grand-wagoneer-limo-offers-22-feed-of-wood-grain-glory" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">stretched Jeep Grand Wagoneer</a> be alright? If none of those are "extra" enough for you, <a href="https://www.mecum.com/lots/SC0520-414630/limo-jet-42-lear-jet/" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">check out this Learjet-turned-road-car</a>. The unbelievable <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/24302/the-stretch-limos-fatal-flaw" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">machine</a> can carry you and 17 of your most curious friends in first-class luxury—that is, <a href="https://www.mecum.com/lots/SC0520-414630/limo-jet-42-lear-jet/" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">should you decide to buy it at Mecum's upcoming Indianapolis auction</a>.</p></div></div><div class="gallery"><div class="gallery__thumbnail" data-position="0"><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/the-drive-cms-content-staging/message-editor%2F1586101686950-screenshot2020-04-05at11.30.36am.png"/><div class="gallery__text"><span class="gallery--credit">Mecum</span></div></div><div class="gallery__thumbnail" data-position="1"><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/the-drive-cms-content-staging/message-editor%2F1586101703237-screenshot2020-04-05at11.30.29am.png"/><div class="gallery__text"><span class="gallery--credit">Mecum</span></div></div><div class="gallery__thumbnail" data-position="2"><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/the-drive-cms-content-staging/message-editor%2F1586101788827-screenshot2020-04-05at11.29.44am.png"/><div class="gallery__text"><span class="gallery--credit">Mecum</span></div></div><span class="gallery__close"><i class="icon icon-close"></i></span><span class="gallery__prev"><i class="icon icon-arrow-previous"></i></span><span class="gallery__next"><i class="icon icon-arrow-next"></i></span></div><div class="has-ad-column"><div class="ad-column"><div class="ad" data-ad-type="colAd"></div></div><div class="articleFragment paragraph"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/32769/the-larger-than-life-tale-of-vini-big-daddy-bergeman-the-limo-king-of-los-angeles" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">limo’s</a> interior is just as flashy as the exterior would suggest, as it features neon lights, an infinity floor, a 42-inch TV, and a 17,000-watt sound system. You and your crew can even enjoy a few drinks from the built-in booze cabinet while cruising around in the 42-foot-long machine, so long as you've hired a designated pilot.&nbsp;</p><p>Amazingly, the jet-car is street legal, but navigating such an awkward vehicle isn't easy. The cockpit has four video monitors to show different angles and cover the massive blind spots around the limo.</p></div><figure class="figure " tabindex="1"><div class="figure-wrapper"><img itemprop="associatedMedia" class="figure-image" src="https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fs3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fthe-drive-cms-content-staging%2Fmessage-editor%252F1586104887887-learmousinegallery1.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=141570a49f1b22f92cc974deeeb5dd9a" alt="" /><div class="credit">Mecum</div></div><button class="gallery-button gallery-previous " title-"Previous" arial-label="Previous"><i class="icon icon-arrow-previous"></i></button><button class="gallery-button gallery-next " title-"Next" arial-label="Next"><i class="icon icon-arrow-next"></i></button><button class="gallery-button gallery-close" title="Close" arial-label="Close"><i class="icon icon-close"></i></button></figure><div class="articleFragment paragraph"><p>The Learjet is still sporting its side-mounted turbine engines, but they're not generating thrust in this application. Instead, power actually heads to the 28-inch rear wheels courtesy of a mid-mounted, 8.1-liter Chevrolet V-8 truck engine. To make the limo more "authentic," there's a speaker system that projects jet sounds when the vehicle is in motion.</p></div><figure class="figure " tabindex="1"><div class="figure-wrapper"><img itemprop="associatedMedia" class="figure-image" src="https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fs3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fthe-drive-cms-content-staging%2Fmessage-editor%252F1586104982658-learmousinegallery3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=2883a8e2aa8aa1d55571288d13b20435" alt="" /><div class="credit">Mecum</div></div><button class="gallery-button gallery-previous " title-"Previous" arial-label="Previous"><i class="icon icon-arrow-previous"></i></button><button class="gallery-button gallery-next " title-"Next" arial-label="Next"><i class="icon icon-arrow-next"></i></button><button class="gallery-button gallery-close" title="Close" arial-label="Close"><i class="icon icon-close"></i></button></figure><div class="articleFragment paragraph"><p>It ended up taking more than two years and $1 million to develop the jet and turn it into a rolling party machine. An Oregon man named Dan Harris dreamed up the creation and recruited Chicago-based Exotic Coach to help build it. Dan developed the concept for the Learmousine in 2005, but it didn’t make an appearance in public until 2018 after an astonishing 40,000 man-hours of custom work. It now belongs to Jettersetter Inc., a company formed by Frank DeAngelo and Michael Kashevatsky.&nbsp;</p></div><figure class="figure " tabindex="1"><div class="figure-wrapper"><img itemprop="associatedMedia" class="figure-image" src="https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fs3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fthe-drive-cms-content-staging%2Fmessage-editor%252F1586104952891-learmousinegallery2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=76c60f02674e0f84f2613ae95eafe6ab" alt="" /><div class="credit">Mecum</div></div><button class="gallery-button gallery-previous " title-"Previous" arial-label="Previous"><i class="icon icon-arrow-previous"></i></button><button class="gallery-button gallery-next " title-"Next" arial-label="Next"><i class="icon icon-arrow-next"></i></button><button class="gallery-button gallery-close" title="Close" arial-label="Close"><i class="icon icon-close"></i></button></figure><div class="articleFragment paragraph"><p>We don’t have an auction price estimate yet, but we do know that the winner won’t have to drive their newly acquired luxo-barge home after the sale. The auction includes a 2015 <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/new-cars/24472/2019-chevy-silverado-test-drive-review-gms-new-full-size-pickup-truck-is-an-all-around-letdown" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Chevy Silverado</a> 2500HD and a 44-foot Iron Bull trailer to haul the plane in order to keep the mileage low and boss-level sky high.</p><p><em>Got a tip? Send us a note: </em><em>tips@thedrive.com</em></p><p>h/t: <a href="https://www.autoblog.com/2020/03/31/learmousine-jet-limo-mecums-indy-2020-auction/" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank"><em>Autoblog</em></a></p></div></div><section class="related-content related-content--rich"><div class="title-message">MORE TO READ</div><ul><li class="related-article" style="background-image:url('https://the-drive.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fapi.thedrive.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2FTriple-axle-lincoln-new.jpg%3Fquality%3D85?w=860&amp;auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=566b5d550419f031033e7aa2b8167401')"><a href="/news/32769/the-larger-than-life-tale-of-vini-big-daddy-bergeman-the-limo-king-of-los-angeles" class="linkable"><div class="related-flag">RELATED</div><div class="title">The Larger-Than-Life Tale of Vini &#39;Big Daddy&#39; Bergeman, the Limo King of Los Angeles</div><div class="dek">The 1980s in Los Angeles: Big hair, big cars, and Big Daddy Bergeman.</div><div class="read-now">READ NOW</div></a></li><li class="related-article" style="background-image:url('https://the-drive-2.imgix.net/https%3A%2F%2Fapi.thedrive.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F00t0t_bH2pFppZQUx_1200x900.jpg%3Fquality%3D85?w=860&amp;auto=compress%2Cformat&amp;ixlib=js-1.4.1&amp;s=63805c7795064a38ffedc8a0880ca70e')"><a href="/news/32532/this-trashed-maserati-quattroporte-iii-limo-is-like-the-sad-end-of-an-e-true-hollywood-story" class="linkable"><div class="related-flag">RELATED</div><div class="title">This Trashed Maserati Quattroporte III